#This shows you how to install VSFTP (the 'd' stands for damon) on your Ubuntu Server. This is for version 16.04
#From your command line


> sudo apt-get install vsftpd


#Enter your root password then hit enter.  You will be asked if you want to install the packages press 'y' to confirm the install.

#Afterwards you will have installed the software. 

